HEADWORD: Loligo
<hw>Lo*li"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., cuttle
fish.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of cephalopods, including
numerous species of squids, common on the coasts of America and Europe.
They are much used for fish bait.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

